To solve this problem, we need to find out how many hours it took for Tom to dry 10 pairs of socks. We can do this by using the information that it took 10 hours for Tom to wash and dry all 10 pairs of socks. Since Tom has already dried 3 pairs of socks, we know that he will need to spend an additional 7/10 of the time it takes to dry a pair of socks to dry the remaining 7 pairs of socks.

So, the total amount of time it took for Tom to dry all 10 pairs of socks was:

10 hours (to wash and dry all 10 pairs) + 7/10 of 10 hours = 10 hours + 7 hours = 17 hours

Therefore, it will take Tom an additional 17 - 10 = 7 hours to dry the remaining 7 pairs of socks.
